post_title: Beware of SCAMMERS, wanting your Credit Card info
post_text:
This letter is to explain that if you click on the listing of a woman you are interested in, it could be a scammer who is fraudulently trying to get you interested, then after having had a certain amount of contact with you, there will be an attempt at trying to somehow get your credit card information.
This is what happened to me. I am trying to rid Craigslist of these scammers in my city of Ventura at least, so that the available listings of women that men can view on Craigslist, will be of actual women seeking men. 
I actually am a man who has a listing in the category of women seeking me, one day I got two replies with different female names, I sent a letter asking why, I got an innocent and believable reply that it was from a lady named Kathy who was a 34 year old teacher's assistant, and that she was trying to be discreet about finding someone. The letter also mentioned all kinds of good sounding stuff about being interested in cuddling but not in a relationship at the moment. 
This scammer told me basically everything that any guy would want to hear, even as far as saying that sex, along with all of its complications was ok.
Also a picture was sent to me by this scammer, it was a picture of a woman that looked all kinds of good to me, and then soon after, the only reply I got was a suggestion for me to go to a site called xxprofile.com, and that this was necessary to confirm that I was who I claimed to be, before we could meet. This xxprofile.com site had a selection of credit cards that I could enter to confirm my identity, and that the charge to my credit card would be zero dollars, the website mentioned this was only a way of confirming my identity, the fraudulent website posed as a way for men and women to have discreet safe affairs, while at the same time knowing who you are getting involved with. Oh yeah, of course this fake xxprofile.com website displayed a picture of a woman that had no shirt on, showing her firm hooters, and was supposedly her profile picture.
My point of view was like, wtf, this lady wants me to confirm my identity by entering my credit card online, I was all kinds of suspicious the whole time I was chatting back and forth with this person, as to whether or not she was actually legit herself, and now this, it seemed way too unlikely to be real, but yet slightly tempting, as I at that point thought this lady might be hotter than I had realized, and I was quite close to scoring.
So I did some research online and found an article that listed of Craigslist scammers who had been doing this Craigslist scam targeting men who are looking for women, the article listed a xprofilex.com site instead of the one I mentioned, but aside from that, the scam has not changed much. Anyway, the online article mentioned that the scam involved an interested person, inputting their credit card information into a website such as that, then a fairly small charge to their account would be made, at not a ridiculous amount so as to be so noticeable, but at around $35, an amount that might easily go unnoticed. 
Anyway, this is the scam, so guys beware.
I would say that it might be a good idea to wonder about any perspective woman's listing, if it mentioned an unusually easy offer of sex, also the mentioning of I will send you're my picture if you send me yours, then if you receive a picture from a woman that is just really super-hot, then you might be suspicious as to why such a good looking woman is needing Craigslist to find men.
As really good looking women can seem to basically take their pick of the many men just bowing down to be the next in line.
This knowledge should keep you aware not to ever enter any credit card info after having chatted with a supposed woman on Craigslist.
The above mentioned scam tactic, is the only one I have encountered so far, but I am sure there are variations to look out for, maybe some scammers might even go as far as to get a guy interested, then to arrange a meeting, then trying to have you bring money to a prepared money jacking, so look out for various types of scam tactics, if you are looking for women on Craigslist.
I figure that no scammers will waste time posting to Ventura after knowing that any men browsing the Women Seeking Men category in this city, has most likely read this.
Anyway, that is it, now you know what to look out for.

post_title: New York wants amnesty for Illegals
post_text:
Illegal aliens in New York could score billions in Medicaid and college-tuition money -- along with driver's licenses, voting rights and even the ability to run for office -- if Democrats win control of the state Senate in November, the Post has learned.
A little-known bill, dubbed "New York is Home," would offer the most sweeping amnesty available anywhere in the country to nearly 3 million noncitizens living in the Empire State.
It would bar police from releasing any information about them to the feds, unless it involves a criminal warrant unrelated to their immigration status.
(  UH,  illegal immigration  IS  a crime ! )
Under the proposed legislation, undocumented immigrants could also apply for professional licenses and serve on juries.
The plan hinges on Democrats -- who now control both the governorship and the state Assembly -- wresting control of the Senate from Republicans, who oppose immigration amnesty.
Bronx Sen. Gustavo Rivera, who is sponsoring the legislation in the upper chamber, said he thinks the bill would be in position to be passed "if we have a stable Democratic majority in the Senate."
He also likened his measure to the campaigns to legalize same-sex marriage and medical marijuana.
"It's something I believe in," Rivera said Sunday night. "It's something the state can do and should do.
Democratic Brooklyn Assemblyman Karim Camara, the chief Assembly sponsor, agreed that taking the Senate was key, saying "The bill would have a better shot at passing with a Democratic Senate."
"I look forward to having a robust conversation about how significant this bill is."
But the GOP plans on using the proposal to warn voters how radical New York would become if Democrats take charge.
Republicans are already referring to it as the "illegal immigrants benefits legislation" and will make the bill their poster child in elections in more conservative upstate and suburban districts.
"This bill could pass if the Democrats are in charge of the Senate. They're out of their minds," said Sen. Marty Golden (R-Brooklyn).
"This is astounding. This undermines our nation's immigration laws and procedures."
Said state Conservative Party chairman Mike Long: "This is absolutely amnesty. It disregards the laws of the United States. It's unconscionable," Long added.
The bill was introduced during the waning days of the legislative session in June, and is backed by immigrant-rights groups including Make the Road New York, the Center for Popular Democracy, and La Fuente.
GOP officials maintain that amnesty for illegal aliens would open the door to fraud and abuse and increase the risk of terrorism.
For example, the bill would let illegals vote in local and state elections, but they would be barred by federal law from voting for presidential or congressional candidates.
